//! ## Purpose
//!
//! RPC-level validation exists to provide **immediate user feedback**. Without this:
//! - Invalid transactions enter mempool
//! - Block builder silently skips them during building
//! - User sees timeout instead of error message
//!
//! With RPC validation:
//! - User gets descriptive error immediately: "TTL exceeds maximum", "executor not registered"
//! - Invalid transactions never enter mempool
//! - Better developer experience
//!
//! ## Shared Validation
//!
//! This module delegates to `ritual_async::validation` for core validation logic that is
//! shared with the builder. This ensures RPC and builder have identical validation semantics.
//!
//! ## Validation Types
//!
//! 1. **Static validation** (stateless): TTL bounds, URL format, model/messages presence
//! 2. **State validation** (on-chain lookup): Executor registration and capability

